The article discusses a memorandum issued by President Barack Obama on January 21, 2009, regarding a pay freeze for senior members of the White House staff. The memorandum states that due to the severe economic stress in the country, it is appropriate for senior officials to forgo pay increases until further notice. The President emphasizes the need for government action to stimulate economic recovery and assist average Americans during this challenging period. He directs the assistant to the president and Chief of Staff to report back with recommendations for implementing the pay freeze within 30 days. The memorandum concludes by stating that it does not create any enforceable rights or benefits against the United States or any other party.